Manage Prediction Definitions and Models

Use the Model Manager to view, configure, and manage prediction definitions and models that have been deployed in your org.

Start Model Manager
Launch Model Manager from the Analytics panel in CRM Analytics Studio.
Upload and Deploy External Machine Learning Models
Operationalize externally built machine learning models by deploying them in Salesforce. Your business scientists can use their preferred modeling tools to design, build, test, and tune their models.
Manage Prediction Definitions
Use the Model Manager to manage prediction definitions in your org.
Handle Live Data Alerts
Live data monitoring detects when your production data contains high levels of missing or out-of-bounds values—indications that your model’s accuracy is declining. Model Manager surfaces alerts so that you can easily see what’s happening in your data.
Manage Models
Use the Model Manager to manage the models associated with your prediction definitions.
Package and Distribute Your Prediction Definitions and Models
Einstein Discovery supports packaging for prediction definitions and models. You can promote prediction definitions from a sandbox to a production environment. You can distribute prediction definitions using managed or unmanaged packages.

Get Predictions in Tableau Calculated Fields
